  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">START alert-Emergency response to IDPs due to intercommunity conflict in BF-OI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(A) Food assistance to 661 HHs through vouchers costing 23.000 FCFA per HH per month. In addition, a cash of 5000 FCFA will be made to the 661 HHs for oil, energy, condiments in Arbinda and Djibo.
(B) Nutrition assistance to 1263 children (6-23 months), 880 PLWDs by distrution of specific flours in Arbinda and Djibo
(C) Shelter and Non-Food Items : Kitchen pots + Solar lamps, Clothes in addition to NFI planned to be distributed by Plan International this week) to 1416 HHs in Basargho and Foube
(D) Protection supports to 1416 HHs covering 
(E) WASH activities benefiting to 761 HHs consisting</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Success in this project will look like:
&#x2022; 14,861 affected and vulnerable people receive cash assistance for food, NFIs, WASH and Protection items that suit them best to meet their basic needs 
&#x2022; 14,861 people will get emergency assistance in a dignified manner as per humanitarian principles and imperative.
&#x2022; 1263 children under under 2 years of age and 880 pregnant and lactating women will protected against the risk of getting under-nourishment.                                                                                                                                                                        
&#x2022; 7,728 females will have access to clean and hygiene sanitation material.
&#x2022; 14,861 people will be consulted and have access to share their feedback and complaints with project management.
&#x2022; Consortium implement the project in compliance with donor&apos;s policy and guidelines.</narrative>
  </description>
